posts.subject: Something changed much for the worse....
posts.body:
Once could post almost 3000ea images at a time using Firefox. Tests now suggest 100ea is the practical limit.

I do believe Firefox did update recently, but have no idea if it is the culprit.  

Linux 64

posts.subject: Sorry, Poindexters broke the tools  :(
posts.body:
Once was able to upload 3000ea images at one time. Now can only upload ~100ea :(  Suspect this is caused by a Firefox update - but it's not worth the squeeze to isolate further.

Oh well, made it to 3 days before the election. Earlier luck was sufficient to post perhaps > 200,000 images here?

Still sad, because 08chan was far superior to other image sharing methods. But without an easy to use loading tool - it's just as bad as everyone else's solution.

Make no mistake, Donald.win IS one hell of a force in this world. But that said, it doesn't offer much to those who just wish to quickly peruse the memes without all the fuss.

Would be a worthy effort for the powers that be. Find a way to fix these things  - then start porting ALL Donaldwin memes and images to Zeronet. Automatically via a script.

Donaldwin can sure do it easier than my independent web scraping effort. But this DOES require both the owner of 08chan and the owners of Donald.win to get off their duff and make this happen.

I'd say 200,000K images is more than a proof of concept? Look at your seed count for proof of audience. There are times when we've seen more than 80ea peers lapping up new postings here. Given the time involved - that suggests rapid peer turnover. So clearly, some people just want the memes.


Goodbye folks. I'm done. Hopefully 08chan and Donaldwin will see the error of their ways.......Not everyone is willing to stay engaged with yabber rich forums like Donaldwin. They just want the memes.

Close to the election....still have 7491ea memes unposted for this session (shaking head).
